div.div:
Add migration for authorization and correct typo in namespaces
This commit introduces a new migration file to create the 'authorization' table in the database. Additionally, it corrects namespaces in several files which previously began with 'app\\Models', but should start with 'App\\Models'. Lastly, it also includes logic for handling terminated user accounts and expired tokens.

Update language files and modify login and signup views
This commit updates the language phrases in the common.php file and alters the interface for both the sign-in and sign-up blade files. The changes mainly concern the labels for captcha and the new account button. The captcha label has been made common for consistency and the new account button has been relocated in the sign-in view.

Add OAuth management and improve authentication checks
Added features for OAuth management including scopes, scope groups, and applications. Established a set of allowed domains and updated the authentication flow to reject logins from unapproved domains. Enhanced the reporting system by extending the collection period to include the previous month's data.
Created new branch main in Fluffici/auth.fluffici.eu
